   - AppState::new() creates broadcast channel (capacity 1024) for SSE

3. crates/server/src/error.rs (NEW)
   - AppError { status, code, message, details }
   - Constructors: bad_request, unauthorized, not_found, conflict, internal
   - IntoResponse impl producing { "error": { "code", "message", "details?" } }
   - From<sqlx::Error> impl
   - Unit tests for constructors

4. crates/server/src/routes/mod.rs (NEW)
   - pub mod health;

5. crates/server/src/routes/health.rs (NEW)
   - health() -> 200 { "status": "ok" }
   - ready(State) -> 200 or 503 based on DB connectivity (SELECT 1)
   - idle(State) -> 200 { "idle": true, "pending_or_assigned_jobs": 0 } or 503 with count

6. crates/server/src/main.rs (MODIFIED - complete rewrite)
   - Modules: config, error, routes, state
   - fallback() -> 404 with standard error JSON
   - build_cors(config) -> CorsLayer (permissive if "*", specific origins otherwise)
     - Allows: GET, POST, PATCH, DELETE, OPTIONS
     - Allows headers: Authorization, Content-Type, X-API-Key
   - build_router(state) -> Router with health routes, fallback, TraceLayer, CorsLayer
   - main(): loads config, init tracing (pretty for dev, JSON for prod based on RUST_LOG),
     creates PgPool, runs migrations, builds router, binds and serves

### Key Design Decisions:

- build_router() is a public function separate from main() to enable testing
- Tracing: if RUST_LOG is not set, assumes dev mode with pretty format and info+tower_http=debug filter
  If RUST_LOG is set, uses JSON format for production
- CORS: if origins is ["*"], uses CorsLayer::permissive(); otherwise parses specific origins
- broadcast channel on AppState for future SSE log streaming (capacity 1024)
- AppError implements From<sqlx::Error> for ergonomic ? usage in handlers

